body: "Releases are date-based and the roadmap has three horizons (simplification+SDK-first, composability+security, scale-out), but nothing defines when pm is 1.0/GA: what surfaces are frozen, what compatibility is promised to script authors, package authors, and SDK integrators, and what scale numbers must hold. Without an explicit stability contract, the zero-spelling-removal alias layer (pm-0z7n) has no defined end state and integrators cannot rely on the SDK surface. This ADR is the capstone that turns the three initiatives' outcomes into a promised contract; it should be drafted after ADRs pm-pbyu and pm-bl8x are accepted."
